  "human_asset_required": "Until the human-asset pipeline drops real Opus files into backend/static/voice/safety/, every slot above is marked status='placeholder'. The backend route /static/voice/safety/<file> returns 503 with header X-Sakha-Asset-Status: placeholder for placeholders. Mobile clients gracefully fall back to wisdom_engine._render_voice (Part 2) which renders the spoken-arc text — TTS'd live in the WSS turn — with no audible difference except the slight first-byte latency cost (still under spec budget). When CI must enforce real audio, set KIAAN_SAFETY_AUDIO_REQUIRED=1 — scripts/validate_safety_audio.py will fail the build."
